      <section eId="sec_CHC-1151">
        <num>CHC 1151</num>
        <heading>1151.  Relinquishment of infants; defense to prosecution</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1151__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the parent is unable to travel to a designated emergency care facility, the parent
may call &quot;911&quot;, and a firefighter, a law enforcement officer, or an emergency medical service
provider shall immediately be dispatched to meet the parent and transport the child to a
hospital and to ensure that all requirements listed in Article 1152(D) through (I) have been
met.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1151__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>Relinquishment of an infant in accordance with this Chapter is not a criminal act
of neglect, abandonment, cruelty, or a crime against the child and shall not be subject to an
investigation for abandonment by the department.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=180649</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
